# Contributing

First of all: thanks for making a contribution.

When contributing to this repository, please discuss the change you'd like to make via a GitHub issue before sending a pull request. This will save time for everyone involved.

In addition to manual testing, we'd greatly prefer if you include unit tests along with your pull requests. Additionally, any pull request you send should not break existing tests.

Finally, all Smyte open-source projects follow the latest [Contributor Covenant](http://contributor-covenant.org/version/1/4/). To report any violations of the code of conduct, email pete at smyte dot com.